Convert search and Drive tools to MCP servers

Search and Drive tools now run as real MCP servers under
mcp-servers/, communicating with research.py over stdio.
research.py is now an MCP client. It discovers tools at
startup instead of importing hardcoded tool definitions.

Notion stays a direct SDK call, not converted to MCP.

Added a circuit breaker. A tool that fails 3 times in a row
gets dropped from the run instead of being retried forever.

Added transport-level error handling. A crashed MCP server
no longer crashes the whole research run.

Removed tools/search.py and tools/drive.py. Their logic now
lives entirely inside the corresponding MCP server.

Updated README and requirements.txt to match.
